01:32:29,210 --> 01:32:33,942
Serifos: Greek island located
in the western Cyclades."

1012
01:32:33,940 --> 01:32:39,314
[In Fr.] - Where did you find that?
- By the river.

1013
01:32:40,571 --> 01:32:44,114
[Fr.] Give it to me. I'll take care of it.

1014
01:32:54,200 --> 01:32:57,600
Can you imagine why I brought you
to such a quiet place today?

1015
01:33:05,210 --> 01:33:06,028
No.

1016
01:33:07,257 --> 01:33:10,000
Because I think it's the perfect spot
for your grave.

1017
01:33:58,857 --> 01:34:00,714
Now cover yourself with soil.

1018
01:34:01,400 --> 01:34:02,771
Use you hands.

1019
01:34:20,371 --> 01:34:21,771
Over your face too.

1020
01:34:21,885 --> 01:34:24,742
You wouldn't want your face to get
eaten by dogs, would you?

1021
01:34:52,085 --> 01:34:55,114
If you die before me,
I'll visit you as often as I can.

1022
01:34:55,710 --> 01:34:57,000
I promise.

1023
01:35:08,390 --> 01:35:10,980
I think we should leave right now.

1024
01:35:12,790 --> 01:35:15,142
The three of us coming here instead of

1025
01:35:16,028 --> 01:35:18,800
two or four is very dangerous.

1026
01:35:20,210 --> 01:35:22,480
Why didn't we think of that earlier?

1027
01:35:23,610 --> 01:35:26,371
Highly likely the doctor will suspect us.

1028
01:35:27,542 --> 01:35:31,100
I suggest that we leave
the first chance we get.

1029
01:35:32,550 --> 01:35:34,142
Right now, in fact.

1030
01:35:35,485 --> 01:35:36,971
Don't be afraid.

1031
01:35:38,171 --> 01:35:39,900
No one will suspect a thing.

1032
01:35:41,330 --> 01:35:43,640
I bet you weren't expecting this surprise.

1033
01:35:45,330 --> 01:35:48,057
- Isn't it wonderful?
- Yes, it is.

1034
01:35:49,330 --> 01:35:52,440
Still, I'd like a few days
just to think it over, so that

1035
01:35:53,885 --> 01:35:58,780
I could maybe have the surgery
when we next come to the city.

1036
01:36:01,510 --> 01:36:03,420
What's there to think about?

1037
01:36:03,828 --> 01:36:07,600
If it's better to see clearly
or to be short-sighted? Is that it?

1038
01:36:09,050 --> 01:36:11,000
That's absurd, you know that.

1039
01:36:11,410 --> 01:36:13,657
Anyway, this doctor is the best there is.

1040
01:36:13,828 --> 01:36:16,460
And it's really very difficult
to get an appointment.

1041
01:36:16,510 --> 01:36:19,180
I called him months ago
to get him to see you today.

1042
01:37:11,550 --> 01:37:12,828
She's blind.

1043
01:37:13,510 --> 01:37:14,742
Thank you.

1044
01:37:41,857 --> 01:37:44,114
Throw down your knife and stand up.

1045
01:37:47,314 --> 01:37:49,880
Why did you have to blind me?

1046
01:37:49,930 --> 01:37:51,800
You could have blinded him.

1047
01:37:52,370 --> 01:37:54,520
I have no idea what you're talking about.

1048
01:37:54,885 --> 01:37:57,000
The drugs are messing with your head.

1049
01:37:57,400 --> 01:38:01,200
If I were you, I would try and be
a little braver about the whole thing.

1050
01:38:01,750 --> 01:38:03,500
Now get up and give me your knife

1051
01:38:04,670 --> 01:38:06,660
or I'll hit you and take it by force.

1052
01:38:08,000 --> 01:38:10,942
- Here I come.
- I swear I'm going to kill you.

1053
01:38:23,514 --> 01:38:26,600
Let go of my hair, you're hurting me.

1054
01:38:46,200 --> 01:38:49,828
Just think, that when someone goes blind

1055
01:38:50,628 --> 01:38:52,700
one of the other senses

1056
01:38:53,714 --> 01:38:55,160
is heightened.

1057
01:39:31,410 --> 01:39:33,742
You could also catch a dog in the woods

1058
01:39:33,857 --> 01:39:35,657
and train it to guide you.

1059
01:39:36,714 --> 01:39:38,514
Dogs can do that, you know.

1060
01:39:39,542 --> 01:39:41,542
I'll help you catch a dog myself.

1061
01:39:43,257 --> 01:39:46,714
Now calm down,
or I'm going to leave you here

1062
01:39:46,714 --> 01:39:50,100
and I don't think you'll manage
to find Meeting Point 2 on your own.

1063
01:40:04,028 --> 01:40:05,714
Are you enjoying the view?

1064
01:40:07,400 --> 01:40:08,485
Sure.

1065
01:40:11,371 --> 01:40:12,857
What happened to your hand?

1066
01:40:14,457 --> 01:40:19,057
I was cutting a tree branch with a knife
and I cut myself by accident.

1067
01:40:19,057 --> 01:40:22,257
You look handsome today,
did you get your hair cut?

1068
01:40:22,485 --> 01:40:23,520
Thank you.

1069
01:40:23,570 --> 01:40:25,228
No, I didn't get a haircut.

1070
01:40:25,530 --> 01:40:27,440
I'm going to get my hair cut today.

1071
01:40:27,771 --> 01:40:29,000
Look what I brought you.

1072
01:40:29,050 --> 01:40:32,657
Oh, thank you so much.
I'm so hungry, I'll eat it right away.

1073
01:40:33,000 --> 01:40:34,700
It's a bigger flashlight.

1074
01:40:34,750 --> 01:40:36,660
Oh, I'm sorry.

1075
01:40:36,710 --> 01:40:39,314
It's so big, I thought it was a rabbit.

1076
01:40:40,057 --> 01:40:42,085
The biggest flashlight I've ever seen.

1077
01:40:42,085 --> 01:40:43,060
Oh.

1078
01:40:44,428 --> 01:40:46,057
Are you ready for tonight?

1079
01:40:46,714 --> 01:40:48,360
Of course I am.

1080
01:40:52,057 --> 01:40:55,171
I want to tell you something
but please don't be angry.

1081
01:40:56,342 --> 01:40:58,140
OK. What's wrong?

1082
01:40:58,690 --> 01:41:00,600
I can't see anything.

1083
01:41:01,970 --> 01:41:03,257
I'm blind.

1084
01:41:03,571 --> 01:41:05,000
What do you mean?

1085
01:41:06,228 --> 01:41:10,080
There's no point in lying to you,
you'll find out sooner or later.

1086
01:41:11,570 --> 01:41:13,942
Our leader blinded me in the city.

1087
01:41:15,000 --> 01:41:19,371
She must have realized
that I love you and you love me

1088
01:41:19,542 --> 01:41:23,285
and that we were going to run away
to the city together.

1089
01:41:25,428 --> 01:41:26,571
I'm sorry.

1090
01:41:29,257 --> 01:41:30,900
You can't see at all?

1091
01:41:32,485 --> 01:41:34,140
No, not at all.

1092
01:41:35,970 --> 01:41:38,080
And when you asked if I'd had my hair cut?

1093
01:41:40,930 --> 01:41:42,840
I was just saying that

1094
01:41:44,714 --> 01:41:47,228
so you wouldn't realize
that I can't see.

1095
01:41:50,171 --> 01:41:51,600
I'm sorry.

1096
01:41:52,485 --> 01:41:53,820
Don't cry.

1097
01:41:53,870 --> 01:41:55,860
Crying will make your eyes hurt more.

1098
01:41:59,857 --> 01:42:01,428
We'll find a way.

1099
01:42:18,930 --> 01:42:20,400
What blood type are you?

1100
01:42:21,610 --> 01:42:22,640
B.

1101
01:42:34,550 --> 01:42:38,028
♪ From the first time I saw her,
I knew she was the one

1102
01:42:38,670 --> 01:42:41,485
♪ As she stared in my eyes and smiled

1103
01:42:42,070 --> 01:42:45,171
♪ And her lips were the color of roses

1104
01:42:45,790 --> 01:42:49,514
♪ That grew down the river
all bloody and wild

1105
01:42:54,142 --> 01:42:56,771
Do you like berries?
Blueberries, blackberries?

1106
01:42:56,771 --> 01:42:58,485
- No, no.
- Mm.

1107
01:43:00,571 --> 01:43:01,885
Can you play the piano?

1108
01:43:02,950 --> 01:43:03,857
No.

1109
01:43:11,542 --> 01:43:12,942
Plastic cup.

1110
01:43:13,142 --> 01:43:15,485
That's right. Very good.

1111
01:43:18,342 --> 01:43:19,714
Do you speak German?

1112
01:43:22,828 --> 01:43:23,800
No.

1113
01:43:25,800 --> 01:43:27,540
I could teach you German.

1114
01:43:28,600 --> 01:43:31,342
But it would take at least a year for you
to be able to speak the basics,

1115
01:43:31,371 --> 01:43:33,200
not fluently, so there's no point.

1116
01:43:33,885 --> 01:43:37,142
You know, German is one of the most
difficult languages in the world to learn,

1117
01:43:37,457 --> 01:43:40,040
because its grammar is very complicated.

1118
01:43:43,885 --> 01:43:44,942
I brought you something.

1119
01:43:47,590 --> 01:43:49,085
It's a fish.

1120
01:43:49,430 --> 01:43:50,314
Oh.

1121
01:43:53,590 --> 01:43:56,428
♪ On the second day,
I brought her a flower

1122
01:43:57,590 --> 01:44:01,057
♪ She was more beautiful
than any woman I'd seen

1123
01:44:01,150 --> 01:44:05,000
♪ And I said,
Do you know where the wild roses grow

1124
01:44:05,290 --> 01:44:08,085
♪ So sweet and scarlet and free

1125
01:44:14,142 --> 01:44:15,120
Kiwi.

1126
01:44:15,170 --> 01:44:18,171
That's right, ten out of ten again.

1127
01:44:20,428 --> 01:44:21,771
Can I give you a kiss?

1128
01:44:25,371 --> 01:44:28,600
I can't thank you enough
for all the activities and games

1129
01:44:28,600 --> 01:44:28,628
and for keeping me company,
I can't thank you enough
for all the activities and games

1130
01:44:28,628 --> 01:44:30,514
and for keeping me company,

1131
01:44:30,514 --> 01:44:33,285
but you know we can't do that any more.

1132
01:44:36,730 --> 01:44:39,914
Would you like to play another round of
Touch-Guess-Think-Win?

1133
01:44:40,057 --> 01:44:42,371
No, that's enough for today.

1134
01:44:44,310 --> 01:44:46,940
In any case, I've run out of things
to test you with.

1135
01:44:47,085 --> 01:44:47,828
Oh.

1136
01:44:48,942 --> 01:44:50,400
Maybe tomorrow

1137
01:44:50,914 --> 01:44:52,960
or one of these days.

1138
01:44:53,010 --> 01:44:54,485
Tomorrow morning?

1139
01:44:55,090 --> 01:44:56,400
We'll see.

1140
01:45:01,350 --> 01:45:03,060
- Bye.
- Bye.

1141
01:45:36,171 --> 01:45:37,571
Good afternoon.

1142
01:45:40,050 --> 01:45:41,371
How are you?

1143
01:45:42,010 --> 01:45:43,057
Fine.

1144
01:45:44,514 --> 01:45:45,714
I'm hungry.

1145
01:45:46,970 --> 01:45:49,120
You haven't brought me a rabbit for days.

1146
01:45:50,885 --> 01:45:52,800
Or things for me to touch and guess.

1147
01:45:54,630 --> 01:45:56,171
I've got good news.

1148
01:45:56,590 --> 01:45:58,285
I've had a great idea.

1149
01:45:59,430 --> 01:46:00,885
Have you a minute?

1150
01:46:01,870 --> 01:46:03,542
What kind of idea?

1151
01:46:06,685 --> 01:46:08,220
I raise my left foot,

1152
01:46:10,370 --> 01:46:13,080
I bring my elbow
to my knee and tap it twice.

1153
01:46:14,450 --> 01:46:17,000
I bring my foot to my knee
and tap it three times.

1154
01:46:17,550 --> 01:46:19,700
I lie face down, I kneel down.

1155
01:46:21,110 --> 01:46:22,685
I touch my left cheek

1156
01:46:23,657 --> 01:46:24,980
and then lie face up.

1157
01:46:31,914 --> 01:46:34,240
Are you sure you're prepared to do that?

1158
01:46:39,610 --> 01:46:41,520
Yes, of course I'm sure.

1159
01:46:42,210 --> 01:46:44,120
I wouldn't propose it otherwise.

1160
01:46:49,428 --> 01:46:50,280
When?

1161
01:46:52,085 --> 01:46:53,080
Tomorrow.

1162
01:46:59,970 --> 01:47:01,171
Tomorrow.

1163
01:48:53,742 --> 01:48:55,514
We should speed up a little.

1164
01:48:58,710 --> 01:49:00,457
I can't go much faster.

1165
01:49:01,170 --> 01:49:03,320
The trousers are too tight. I'm sorry.

1166
01:49:04,570 --> 01:49:06,600
It was dark and I couldn't see clearly.

1167
01:49:07,150 --> 01:49:09,060
And I didn't have time to try them on.

1168
01:49:10,057 --> 01:49:11,085
I'm sorry.

1169
01:49:13,628 --> 01:49:14,800
Never mind.

1170
01:49:18,428 --> 01:49:19,971
There's a bus coming.

1171
01:49:44,857 --> 01:49:46,400
It was the hotel coach.

1172
01:49:47,285 --> 01:49:48,657
They didn't see us.

1173
01:50:14,685 --> 01:50:15,771
Profile.

1174
01:50:26,514 --> 01:50:27,571
Fingers.

1175
01:50:35,771 --> 01:50:36,857
Elbows.

1176
01:50:57,000 --> 01:50:59,114
Would you like me to show you my belly?

1177
01:50:59,200 --> 01:51:00,257
No.

1178
01:51:01,000 --> 01:51:03,228
I, I remember your belly very well.

1179
01:51:06,730 --> 01:51:07,857
Smile.

1180
01:51:26,870 --> 01:51:30,580
Can I have a knife and fork, please?
Not a butter knife, a steak knife.

1181
01:51:30,742 --> 01:51:31,600
Certainly.

1182
01:51:45,942 --> 01:51:46,857
Thank you.

1183
01:51:56,514 --> 01:51:58,200
I'm going to do it with a knife.

1184
01:51:58,914 --> 01:52:00,628
Do you want me to come with you?

1185
01:52:00,885 --> 01:52:02,371
I'd rather you didn't.

1186
01:52:03,730 --> 01:52:04,942
Don't worry.

1187
01:52:06,057 --> 01:52:09,171
It's strange at first,
but then you get used to it.

1188
01:52:10,285 --> 01:52:12,420
And your other senses are heightened --

1189
01:52:12,470 --> 01:52:15,228
touch, for example, and hearing.

1190
01:52:16,030 --> 01:52:17,114
I know.

1191
01:52:28,028 --> 01:52:29,457
I won't be long.

1192
01:53:57,114 --> 01:53:58,514
Thank you very much.

